<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-11T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-11T07:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.151/141: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Aldridge</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-11T14:00:00+02:00">July 11, 1935—2
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 11—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>94. Department’s 45, July 5, 7 p.m. I have seen Mr. Tsaldaris, Prime
                                Minister and Minister for Foreign Affairs. He promised me to give
                                the matter his personal attention.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Aldridge</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>